#: ../../../reference/c-api/datetimes.rst:2
msgid "Datetime API"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/datetimes.rst:4
msgid ""
"NumPy represents dates internally using an int64 counter and a unit metadata "
"struct. Time differences are represented similarly using an int64 and a unit "
"metadata struct. The functions described below are available to to "
"facilitate converting between ISO 8601 date strings, NumPy datetimes, and "
"Python datetime objects in C."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/datetimes.rst:11
msgid "Data types"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/datetimes.rst:13
msgid ""
"In addition to the :c:type:`npy_datetime` and :c:type:`npy_timedelta` "
"typedefs for :c:type:`npy_int64`, NumPy defines two additional structs that "
"represent time unit metadata and an \"exploded\" view of a datetime."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/datetimes.rst:19
msgid "Represents datetime unit metadata."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/datetimes.rst:21
msgid ""
"typedef struct {\n"
"    NPY_DATETIMEUNIT base;\n"
"    int num;\n"
"} PyArray_DatetimeMetaData;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/datetimes.rst:30
msgid "The unit of the datetime."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/datetimes.rst:34
msgid "A multiplier for the unit."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/datetimes.rst:38
msgid "An \"exploded\" view of a datetime value"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/datetimes.rst:40
msgid ""
"typedef struct {\n"
"    npy_int64 year;\n"
"    npy_int32 month, day, hour, min, sec, us, ps, as;\n"
"} npy_datetimestruct;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/datetimes.rst:49
msgid ""
"Time units supported by NumPy. The \"FR\" in the names of the enum variants "
"is short for frequency."
msgstr ""

