#: ../../../reference/c-api/datetimes.rst:114
msgid "Conversion functions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/datetimes.rst:120
msgid ""
"Converts a datetime from a datetimestruct to a datetime in the units "
"specified by the unit metadata. The date is assumed to be valid."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/datetimes.rst:123
msgid ""
"If the ``num`` member of the metadata struct is large, there may be integer "
"overflow in this function."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/datetimes.rst:126
#: ../../../reference/c-api/datetimes.rst:135
msgid "Returns 0 on success and -1 on failure."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/datetimes.rst:132
msgid ""
"Converts a datetime with units specified by the unit metadata to an exploded "
"datetime struct."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/datetimes.rst:141
msgid ""
"Tests for and converts a Python ``datetime.datetime`` or ``datetime.date`` "
"object into a NumPy ``npy_datetimestruct``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/datetimes.rst:144
msgid ""
"``out_bestunit`` gives a suggested unit based on whether the object was a "
"``datetime.date`` or ``datetime.datetime`` object."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/datetimes.rst:147
msgid ""
"If ``apply_tzinfo`` is 1, this function uses the tzinfo to convert to UTC "
"time, otherwise it returns the struct with the local time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/datetimes.rst:150
msgid ""
"Returns -1 on error, 0 on success, and 1 (with no error set) if obj doesn't "
"have the needed date or datetime attributes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/datetimes.rst:158
msgid "Parses (almost) standard ISO 8601 date strings. The differences are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/datetimes.rst:160
msgid ""
"The date \"20100312\" is parsed as the year 20100312, not as equivalent to "
"\"2010-03-12\". The '-' in the dates are not optional."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/datetimes.rst:162
msgid ""
"Only seconds may have a decimal point, with up to 18 digits after it "
"(maximum attoseconds precision)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/datetimes.rst:164
msgid ""
"Either a 'T' as in ISO 8601 or a ' ' may be used to separate the date and "
"the time. Both are treated equivalently."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/datetimes.rst:166
msgid "Doesn't (yet) handle the \"YYYY-DDD\" or \"YYYY-Www\" formats."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/datetimes.rst:167
msgid "Doesn't handle leap seconds (seconds value has 60 in these cases)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/datetimes.rst:168
msgid "Doesn't handle 24:00:00 as synonym for midnight (00:00:00) tomorrow"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/datetimes.rst:169
msgid ""
"Accepts special values \"NaT\" (not a time), \"Today\", (current day "
"according to local time) and \"Now\" (current time in UTC)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/datetimes.rst:172
msgid ""
"``str`` must be a NULL-terminated string, and ``len`` must be its length."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/datetimes.rst:174
msgid ""
"``unit`` should contain -1 if the unit is unknown, or the unit which will be "
"used if it is."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/datetimes.rst:177
msgid ""
"``casting`` controls how the detected unit from the string is allowed to be "
"cast to the 'unit' parameter."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/datetimes.rst:180
msgid "``out`` gets filled with the parsed date-time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/datetimes.rst:182
msgid ""
"``out_bestunit`` gives a suggested unit based on the amount of resolution "
"provided in the string, or -1 for NaT."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/datetimes.rst:185
msgid ""
"``out_special`` gets set to 1 if the parsed time was 'today', 'now', empty "
"string, or 'NaT'. For 'today', the unit recommended is 'D', for 'now', the "
"unit recommended is 's', and for 'NaT' the unit recommended is 'Y'."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/datetimes.rst:190
msgid "Returns 0 on success, -1 on failure."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/datetimes.rst:195
msgid ""
"Returns the string length to use for converting datetime objects with the "
"given local time and unit settings to strings. Use this when constructing "
"strings to supply to ``NpyDatetime_MakeISO8601Datetime``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/datetimes.rst:205
msgid ""
"Converts an ``npy_datetimestruct`` to an (almost) ISO 8601 NULL-terminated "
"string. If the string fits in the space exactly, it leaves out the NULL "
"terminator and returns success."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/datetimes.rst:209
msgid ""
"The differences from ISO 8601 are the 'NaT' string, and the number of year "
"digits is >= 4 instead of strictly 4."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/datetimes.rst:212
msgid ""
"If ``local`` is non-zero, it produces a string in local time with a +-#### "
"timezone offset. If ``local`` is zero and ``utc`` is non-zero, produce a "
"string ending with 'Z' to denote UTC. By default, no time zone information "
"is attached."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/datetimes.rst:217
msgid ""
"``base`` restricts the output to that unit. Set ``base`` to -1 to auto-"
"detect a base after which all the values are zero."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/datetimes.rst:220
msgid ""
"``tzoffset`` is used if ``local`` is enabled, and ``tzoffset`` is set to a "
"value other than -1. This is a manual override for the local time zone to "
"use, as an offset in minutes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/datetimes.rst:224
msgid ""
"``casting`` controls whether data loss is allowed by truncating the data to "
"a coarser unit. This interacts with ``local``, slightly, in order to form a "
"date unit string as a local time, the casting must be unsafe."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/datetimes.rst:229
msgid ""
"Returns 0 on success, -1 on failure (for example if the output string was "
"too short)."
msgstr ""
